<div>
  <h3>Perceived Bitterness</h3>
  <em>Pronounced: 25 - 40 IBUs</em>
</div>

<br>

<div>
  <h3>Alcohol</h3>
  <em>Normal Alcohol Content: 4.5 - 6.2% ABV</em>
</div>

<br>

<div>
  <h3>Flavor and Balance</h3>
  <em>Amber ales have the evident citrus-pine hoppiness of American Pale Ale with a richer malt base that
      includes dark caramel and deeply toasted flavors. Thus both malt and hops are medium to high in flavor
      impact.</em>
</div>

<br>

<div>
  <h3>Related Styles</h3>
  <em>American Pale Ale</em>
</div>

<br>

<div>
  <h3>Beer Reviews</h3>
    <% if @beer_style.length == 0 %>
      <em><%= "There have been no beers entered for this style." %></em>
    <% else %>
    <% @beer_style.each do |b| %>
      <% s_name = DATABASE.execute("SELECT style FROM styles WHERE id = #{b.style_id}") %>
      <% style_name = s_name[0].values[0] %>
      <% b_name = DATABASE.execute("SELECT brewery FROM breweries WHERE id = #{b.brewery_id}") %>
      <% brewery_name = b_name[0].values[0] %>
      <em><h4><%=b.beer%></h4>  
        <ul>
          <li><%= "Style - #{style_name}" %></li> 
          <li><%= "Color - #{b.color}" %></li> 
          <li><%= "IBUs - #{b.ibu}" %></li> 
          <li><%= "ABV - #{b.abv}%" %></li>
          <li><%= "Brewery - #{brewery_name}" %></li> 
          <li><%= "Review - #{b.review}" %></li>
          <li><%= "Date - #{b.date}" %></li></em>
        </ul>
      <% end %>
    <% end %>
</div>

